Title: Fraser Range - Zanthus Geochem-Gravity (P199863), gravity point data
Abstract: Gravity data measures small changes in gravity due to changes in the density of rocks beneath the Earth's surface. The data collected are processed via standard methods to ensure the response recorded is that due only to the rocks in the ground. The results produce datasets that can be interpreted to reveal the geological structure of the sub-surface. The processed data is checked for quality by GA geophysicists to ensure that the final data released by GA are fit-for-purpose. This Fraser Range - Zanthus Geochem-Gravity (P199863) contains a total of 1243 point data values acquired at a spacing of 4000 metres. The data is located in WA and were acquired in 1998, under project No. 199863 for Australian Geological Survey Organisation (AGSO); Geological Survey of Western Australia (GSWA).

Lineage: This Fraser Range - Zanthus Geochem-Gravity (P199863), gravity point data contains ground gravity point data for the Fraser Range - Zanthus Geochem-Gravity (P199863) survey acquired for Australian Geological Survey Organisation (AGSO); Geological Survey of Western Australia (GSWA). This dataset contains a total of 1243 point data values. The data is located in WA and were acquired in 1998. The point located data were collected in irregular grid layout at an average station spacing of 4000 metres. Terrain corrections were calculated using the INTREPID Geophysics software package. The processed data are checked by GA geophysicists using standard methods for assessing quality to ensure that the final data are fit-for-purpose. All data are provided in EPSG:4283 coordinates, Australian Height Datum (AHD) and gravity datum of AAGD07. The units are degrees, meters, and micrometres per second squared, respectively. Reference: Intrepid Geophysics, http://www.intrepid-geophysics.com.

The results produce datasets that can be interpreted to reveal the geological structure of the sub-surface. The processed data is checked for quality by GA geophysicists to ensure that the final data released by GA are fit-for-purpose. This Tookanooka Gravity Traverses 2000, Qld (P200042) contains a total of 102 point data values acquired at a spacing between 200 and 1000 metres. The data is located in QLD and were acquired in 2000, under project No. 200042 for Geological Survey of Queensland (GSQ).

Title: Eastern Goldfields - Lake Carey (P200063), gravity point data
Abstract: Gravity data measures small changes in gravity due to changes in the density of rocks beneath the Earth's surface. The data collected are processed via standard methods to ensure the response recorded is that due only to the rocks in the ground. The results produce datasets that can be interpreted to reveal the geological structure of the sub-surface. The processed data is checked for quality by GA geophysicists to ensure that the final data released by GA are fit-for-purpose. This Eastern Goldfields - Lake Carey (P200063) contains a total of 5254 point data values acquired at a spacing of 1000 metres. The data is located in WA and were acquired in 2000, under project No. 200063 for Australian Geological Survey Organisation (AGSO).
